Awkward Array is a library for manipulating lists, nested records, missing data and
mixed types with NumPy-like idioms. It has built-in support for Numba acceleration,
JAX autodiff, Apache Arrow and ROOT RDataFrame interoperability, and GPUs.
Uproot is a pure Python implementation of ROOT I/O, reading and writing TTrees and
RNTuples as arrays: NumPy, Awkward, and Pandas. Uproot gets histograms through
hist, remote data through fsspec, and uses dask-awkward and awkward-pandas.
